{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17632273","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17632273"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:38:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:38:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17428"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17428","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17428"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10118"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70763"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10118","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10118"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17428"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56229"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5349"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23718"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23796"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70763","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70763"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EEnvironmental pollution from improper garbage disposal is a significant public health concern. Various types of waste have different environmental impacts and decomposition times.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following types of garbage poses the greatest long-term environmental threat to marine ecosystems?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Food scraps","Glass bottles","Metal cans","Plastic debris","Paper waste"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPlastic debris\u003C/strong\u003E poses the most significant long-term threat to marine ecosystems for several reasons:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EIt persists in the environment for hundreds of years\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EBreaks down into microplastics that enter the food chain\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EIs frequently ingested by marine animals causing death\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EReleases toxic chemicals as it degrades\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAccumulates in ocean gyres forming large garbage patches\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options have less severe environmental impacts:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFood scraps\u003C/strong\u003E decompose rapidly and can be metabolised by marine organisms as part of natural nutrient cycling.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGlass bottles\u003C/strong\u003E remain chemically inert in marine environments and do not release harmful substances, though they may pose physical hazards.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMetal cans\u003C/strong\u003E eventually oxidise and decompose into basic elements that occur naturally in marine environments.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPaper waste\u003C/strong\u003E biodegrades within two to six weeks in marine environments through natural bacterial processes.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe persistence and toxicity of plastics, combined with their tendency to fragment into microplastics that can be ingested at all levels of the food chain, makes them particularly harmful to marine ecosystems.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Plastic waste takes hundreds of years to decompose in the environment and breaks down into harmful microplastics.","Marine animals frequently mistake plastic debris for food, leading to injury, starvation and death.","Proper waste segregation and recycling can significantly reduce environmental pollution from garbage."],"references":["Siddiqua A, Hahladakis JN, Al-Attiya WAKA. An overview of the environmental pollution and health effects associated with waste landfilling and open dumping. Environ Sci Pollut Res Int. 2022;29(39):58514-58536. doi:10.1007/s11356-022-21578-z","Shultz JM, Sullivan LM, Galea S. Public Health: An Introduction to the Science and Practice of Population Health. Springer Publishing Company; 2021."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56229"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17428"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56229","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56229"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T13:51:12+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T13:52:02+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10118"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70763"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"i